us  Swimming has been off-limits in the long-polluted Seine River in Paris for more than a century.\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 1291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1119, \"end\": 1138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Winnipeg_Free_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Winnipeg Free Press\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Winnipeg_Free_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Winnipeg_Free_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 1196, \"end\": 1204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6358516668169035e-14, \"text\": \"Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\"}, {\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999989354365, \"rank\": 1.064771557140812e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So with Olympic swimming events on tap for the river, the city poured in $1.5 billion (1.4 billion euros) to try to clean it up.\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1420, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read this article for free:    Already have an account?Log in here \\u00bb  To continue reading, please subscribe:  $0 for the first 4 weeks*  *No charge for 4 weeks then price increases to the regular rate of $19.00 plus GST every four weeks.\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Offer available to new and qualified returning subscribers only.\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1724, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cancel any time.\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"$4.75/week*  *Billed as $19 plus GST every four weeks.\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cancel any time.\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To continue reading, please subscribe:  $1 for the first 4 weeks*  No thanks  *Your next subscription payment will increase by $1.00 and you will be charged $16.99 plus GST for four weeks.\", \"from\": 1816, \"to\": 2004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After four weeks, your payment will increase to $23.99 plus GST every four weeks.\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming has been off-limits in the long-polluted Seine River in Paris for more than a century.\", \"from\": 2088, \"to\": 2183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2153, \"end\": 2158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999989354365, \"rank\": 1.064771557140812e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So with Olympic swimming events on tap for the river, the city poured in $1.5 billion (1.4 billion euros) to try to clean it up.\", \"from\": 2184, \"to\": 2312, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read unlimited articles for free today:    Already have an account?Log in here \\u00bb  Hey there, time traveller!This article was published30/07/2024(490 days ago), so information in it may no longer be current.\", \"from\": 2314, \"to\": 2520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming has been off-limits in the long-polluted Seine River in Paris for more than a century.\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2587, \"end\": 2592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999989354365, \"rank\": 1.064771557140812e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So with Olympic swimming events on tap for the river, the city poured in $1.5 billion (1.4 billion euros) to try to clean it up.\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2746, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With the Paris Games underway, officials are keeping a close eye on water quality.\", \"from\": 2748, \"to\": 2830, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes could feel health effects from swimming in a river with higher-than-accepted levels of E. coli or other bacteria.\", \"from\": 2831, \"to\": 2953, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are key things to know:  What made the Seine so dirty?\", \"from\": 2955, \"to\": 3014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2999, \"end\": 3004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999959463580431, \"rank\": 4.0536581922371826e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris, like many old cities around the world, has a combined sewer system, which means that the city's wastewater and stormwater flow through the same pipes.\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3016, \"end\": 3021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999989354365, \"rank\": 1.064771557140812e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With heavy or prolonged periods of rain, the pipes can get overwhelmed and untreated wastewater flows into the river instead of to a treatment plant.\", \"from\": 3174, \"to\": 3323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That could mean bacteria, viruses or parasites get in the water, said Dr. Nicole Iovine, an infectious disease specialist at University of Florida Health in Gainesville.\", \"from\": 3325, \"to\": 3494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3406, \"end\": 3412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Iovine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.6242550185052806e-21, \"text\": \"Iovine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Iovine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Iovine\"}, {\"begin\": 3482, \"end\": 3493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainesville,_Florida\", \"score\": 0.93643673275069, \"rank\": 0.05354165628922331, \"text\": \"Gainesville\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainesville,_Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainesville,_Florida\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it's not just from human waste.\", \"from\": 3495, \"to\": 3530, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's also the wildlife - rodents, for example.\", \"from\": 3532, \"to\": 3579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When it rains a lot, all of that from those animals can end up in the Seine,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3580, \"to\": 3667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3650, \"end\": 3655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999959463580431, \"rank\": 4.0536581922371826e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What did Paris do to clean up?\", \"from\": 3669, \"to\": 3699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3678, \"end\": 3683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999989354365, \"rank\": 1.064771557140812e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To prepare for the Paris Games, the city built a giant basin to capture excess rainwater and keep untreated waste from flowing into the river, renovated the sewage system and upgraded water treatment plants.\", \"from\": 3701, \"to\": 3908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heavy rain may still swamp the system.\", \"from\": 3910, \"to\": 3948, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The city of Paris has done a lot of work to clean up the Seine, but they can not control the weather,\\\" Iovine said.\", \"from\": 3950, \"to\": 4066, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3963, \"end\": 3968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999989354365, \"rank\": 1.064771557140812e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4008, \"end\": 4013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999959463580431, \"rank\": 4.0536581922371826e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rain over the Olympics opening weekend filled up 20% of the basin, so the contamination levels afterward likely came from wastewater upstream, city officials said.\", \"from\": 4068, \"to\": 4235, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What germs are in the river?\", \"from\": 4237, \"to\": 4265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Water quality tests in June revealed unsafe levels of E. coli bacteria, though results in early July showed improvement.\", \"from\": 4267, \"to\": 4387, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"E. coli is found in human and animal digestive tracts and waste.\", \"from\": 4388, \"to\": 4452, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Most strains are not harmful, Iovine said, but high numbers can indicate dangerous bacteria.\", \"from\": 4453, \"to\": 4545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4483, \"end\": 4489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Iovine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.6242550185052806e-21, \"text\": \"Iovine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Iovine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Iovine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A monitoring group does daily tests at four spots for E. coli as well as enterococci bacteria, which can signal fecal matter and potentially disease-carrying germs.\", \"from\": 4547, \"to\": 4711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The World Triathlon Federation has deemed E. coli levels beyond 900 colony-forming units per 100 milliliters are unsafe.\", \"from\": 4713, \"to\": 4833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4717, \"end\": 4732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"score\": 0.999999999391548, \"rank\": 6.08232237634573e-10, \"text\": \"World Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not a \\\"magic\\\" number though, Iovine said, and officials likely take into account additional factors - like the weather - when making decisions about the water quality.\", \"from\": 4835, \"to\": 5007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4869, \"end\": 4875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Iovine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.6242550185052806e-21, \"text\": \"Iovine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Iovine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Iovine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On a sunny day, the sun's ultraviolet rays can kill the bacteria and lower levels.\", \"from\": 5009, \"to\": 5091, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What happens when you swim in contaminated water?\", \"from\": 5093, \"to\": 5142, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming in water with unsafe levels of bacteria can lead to an upset stomach and intestinal problems.\", \"from\": 5144, \"to\": 5246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimmers may inadvertently swallow the water or pick up infections through open cuts.\", \"from\": 5247, \"to\": 5332, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even a mouthful of contaminated water can lead to diarrhea, and germs can cause illnesses such as infections in the urinary tract or in the intestines, or in the worst-case scenario, life-threatening sepsis.\", \"from\": 5334, \"to\": 5541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The athletes are young, and they are in the best shape of anybody, so they are gonna be more resilient than many of us,\\\" Iovine said.\", \"from\": 5543, \"to\": 5677, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But that does not mean that they can not get sick from these things.\\\"\", \"from\": 5678, \"to\": 5748, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"___  Bose reported from Jackson, Mississippi.\", \"from\": 5750, \"to\": 5795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5774, \"end\": 5794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackson_Bandits\", \"score\": 0.9994022346104147, \"rank\": 0.0005981229266642679, \"text\": \"Jackson, Mississippi\", \"types\": [\"Q4498974\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackson_Bandits\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackson_Bandits\"}, {\"begin\": 5774, \"end\": 5794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackson_Bandits\", \"score\": 0.9994022346104147, \"rank\": 0.0005981229266642679, \"text\": \"Jackson, Mississippi\", \"types\": [\"Q4498974\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackson_Bandits\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackson_Bandits\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AP reporter Kate Brumback contributed from Paris.\", \"from\": 5796, \"to\": 5845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5796, \"end\": 5798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999996646679954, \"rank\": 3.3501130069665753e-07, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 5808, \"end\": 5812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9226609424615662, \"rank\": 0.0838216914023633, \"text\": \"Kate\", \"types\": [\"Q